Notice the space before `*` is gone in the comments, there is 3 space indentation for single indents, 1 tab + 3 space indent for double indents.

- debug a simple node program "Node" that stops on a breakpoint, e.g.:
  ```js
  console.log("Node");
  ```
- start a second debug-session with this program "Looper" (and no breakpoint):
  ```js
  var x = 0;
  setInterval(() => {
	console.log("hello: " + x++);
  }, 1000);
  ```
Observe:
The debug action floater doesn't show "Looper" in the drop down menu but remains on "Node". A user would expect that the drop down shows the program launched last.

- switch to "Looper"
- press pause button

Observe:
The THREAD/CALLSTACK viewer shows that "Looper" is paused but it does not expand the stack:
![2017-07-05_23-49-48](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1898161/27886522-b9bdd19e-61dc-11e7-89b0-b126f8d4c6ea.png)

A user would expect to see this expanded view with the reason for the empty stacktrace:
![2017-07-05_23-52-57](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1898161/27886611-2d5b6256-61dd-11e7-9367-7596987c0648.png)
